<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 19 at 3:15PM HST  by NWS Honolulu</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Hawaii in Hawaii
County through 345 PM HST...
At 315 PM HST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Halaula and Hawi, or 40 miles north of Kailua-Kona, moving northeast
at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kapaau, Pololu Valley, Kohala Ranch, Hawi, Halaula, Waimanu Valley
and Kawaihae.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM HST for
Hawaii.</instruction>
